title: Dallas Stars
complex: The Dallas Stars are a professional ice hockey team based in Dallas, Texas. <s> They are members of the Central Division of the Western Conference of the National Hockey League (NHL). <s> The team was founded during the 1967 NHL expansion as the Minnesota North Stars, based in Bloomington, Minnesota. <s> Before the beginning of the 1978–79 NHL season, the team merged with the Cleveland Barons after the league granted them permission due to each team's respective financial struggles. <s> Ultimately, the franchise relocated to Dallas for the 1993–94 NHL season. <s> The Stars played out of Reunion Arena from their relocation until 2001, when the team moved less than 1.5 miles into the American Airlines Center.
simple: The Dallas Stars are a professional ice hockey team based in Dallas, Texas. <s> They play in the National Hockey League (NHL). <s> The team began in the autumn of 1967, as the Minnesota North Stars. <s> After the 1992-1993 season, the team moved to Dallas.

title: Malik Khizar Hayat Tiwana
complex: Lieutenant-Colonel Sir Malik Khizar Hayat Tiwana (7 August 1900 - 20 January 1975) was a Pakistani statesman, army officer, and landowner who served as the Unionist Premier of the Punjab between 1942 and 1947. <s> Khizar was born at Chak Muzaffarabad, in the district of Sargodha, Punjab in 1900. <s> He was born into the Tiwana clan Jat family of Shahpur and his father Sir Umar Hayat Khan was a wealthy landowner and soldier who was an elected member of the Council of the Secretary of State for India. <s> He was educated at Aitchison College in Lahore.
simple: Malik Sir Khizar Hayat Tiwana (1900-1975), KCSI, OBE, was a Punjabi politician of British India. <s> He remained Premier of the Punjab region during 1942-47, just before the Partition and Independence of India and Pakistan. <s> He was from a Tiwana Rajput landowning family which had been prominent since the 15th-16th centuries AD. <s> His father Malik Sir Umar Hayat Tiwana had also been a faithful vassal of the British Raj and did much to elevate the family further.

title: Jeffrey Moussaieff Masson
complex: Jeffrey Moussaieff Masson (born March 28, 1941 as Jeffrey Lloyd Masson) is an American author. <s> Masson is best known for his conclusions about Sigmund Freud and psychoanalysis.
simple: Jeffrey Masson (born 1941) is a psychotherapist and historian of psychotherapy who wrote a controversial book, "", about Austrian neurologist Sigmund Freud.

title: Huntington, New York
complex: The Town of Huntington is one of ten towns in Suffolk County, New York, United States. <s> Founded in 1653, it is located on the north shore of Long Island in northwestern Suffolk County, with Long Island Sound to its north and Nassau County adjacent to the west. <s> Huntington is part of the New York metropolitan area. <s> As of the United States 2010 Census, the town population was 203,264.
simple: The Town of Huntington is a town in Suffolk County, New York, United States. <s> It was founded in 1653. <s> It is located on the north shore of Long Island. <s> Huntington is part of the New York metropolitan area. <s> As of the United States 2010 Census, the town population was 203,264.

title: Wilsonville, Nebraska
complex: Wilsonville is a village in Furnas County, Nebraska, United States. <s> The population was 93 at the 2010 census.
simple: Wilsonville is a village in Furnas County, Nebraska, United States. <s> The population was 93 at the 2010 census.

title: Härnösand Cathedral
complex: Härnösand Cathedral serves the Diocese of Härnösand and was built in 1846.
simple: Belonging to Härnösand Cathedral Parish of the Church of Sweden, it serves the Diocese of Härnösand, and was opened in 1846.

title: St Pancras Church, Ipswich
complex: Saint Pancras is an active Roman Catholic parish church serving the town centre of Ipswich, England. <s> The neo-gothic church was built as part of the British Catholic revival in the nineteenth century, and was the target of anti-Catholic riots soon after completion.
simple: Saint Pancras is a Catholic church covering the town centre of Ipswich, England.

title: View of Delft
complex: View of Delft is an oil painting by Johannes Vermeer, painted ca. 1660–1661. <s> The painting of the Dutch artist's hometown is among his most popular, painted at a time when cityscapes were uncommon. <s> It is one of three known paintings of Delft by Vermeer, along with "The Little Street" and the lost painting "House Standing in Delft". <s> The use of pointillism in the work suggests that it postdates "The Little Street", and the absence of bells in the tower of the New Church dates it to 1660–1661. <s> Vermeer's "View of Delft" has been held in the Dutch Royal Cabinet of Paintings at the Mauritshuis in The Hague since its establishment in 1822. <s> In 2011, the painting was featured on gold and silver commemorative coins issued by the Royal Dutch Mint.
simple: View of Delft (c.1660-1661) is an oil painting. <s> It was painted by Johannes Vermeer. <s> The painting shows Vermeer's hometown. <s> It is one of his most popular pictures. <s> It is one of three paintings of Delft by Vermeer. <s> The others are "The Little Street" and the lost painting "House Standing in Delft". <s> In 2011, the painting was featured on gold and silver commemorative coins issued by the Royal Dutch Mint.

title: Hugo Ballesteros Reyes
complex: Hugo Eugenio Ballesteros Reyes (3 January 1931 – 7 April 2019) was a Chilean politician and diplomat. <s> Born in Santiago, he studied law at the Universidad de Chile's campus in Valparaíso. <s> He served as a member of the Chamber of Deputies (1957–1969) and the Senate (1969–1973). <s> In 1964 he was also a member of his country's delegation to the United Nations General Assembly. <s> Ballesteros Reyes died of brain cancer in Valparaíso, at the age of 88.
simple: Hugo Eugenio Ballesteros Reyes (3 January 1931 – 7 April 2019) was a Chilean politician and diplomat. <s> He was born in Santiago. <s> He served as a member of the Senate from 1957 to 1965. <s> He was also a member of the Chamber of Deputies from 1969 to 1977. <s> Ballesteros Reyes died of brain cancer on 7 April 2019 in Valparaíso.

title: Ganbareh
complex: "Ganbareh" is a song by German production group Sash! <s> It was released on June 24, 2002 via Virgin Records as the first single from their fourth studio album "S4!Sash!".
simple: "Ganbareh" is a 2002 song by the German DJ group Sash!. <s> It is the first single from their fourth studio album "S4!Sash!" <s> which was released on 24 June 2002.

title: Poitou
complex: Poitou ( , , ] ; Poitevin: "Poetou") was a province of west-central France whose capital city was Poitiers. <s> There is a marshland called the Poitevin Marsh (French "Marais Poitevin") on the Gulf of Poitou, on the west coast of France, just north of La Rochelle and west of Niort. <s> Many of the Acadians who settled in what is now Nova Scotia beginning in 1604, and later in New Brunswick, came from the region of Poitou. <s> After the Acadians were deported by the British beginning in 1755, some of them eventually took refuge in Québec. <s> A large portion of these refugees were also deported to Louisiana in 1785 and eventually became known as Cajuns (from Acadians).
simple: Poitou was a province of France of west-central France whose capital city was Poitiers. <s> There is a marshland called the Poitevin Mar on the Gulf of Poitou, on the west coast of France, just north of La Rochelle and west of Niort. <s> Many of the Acadians who settled in what is now Nova Scotia beginning in 1604 and later to New Brunswick, came from the region of Poitou. <s> After the Acadians were deported by the British beginning in 1755, a number of Acadians eventually took refuge in Poitou and in Québec. <s> A large portion of these refugees also migrated to Louisiana in 1785 and following years became known as Cajuns.

title: Zuienkerke
complex: Zuienkerke (] ) is a municipality located in the Belgian province of West Flanders. <s> The municipality comprises the towns of Houtave, Meetkerke, Nieuwmunster and Zuienkerke proper.
simple: Zuienkerke is a municipality in the Belgian province of West Flanders.

title: Motocross
complex: Motocross is a form of off-road motorcycle racing held on enclosed off-road circuits. <s> The sport evolved from motorcycle trials competitions held in the United Kingdom. <s> It is very physically demanding, especially for the passenger. <s> This is reflected in most in the Swedish term for passenger, "burkslav", roughly translated as trunk/barrel-slave.
simple: Motocross is a form of motorcycle racing. <s> The sport came from motorcycle trials competitions held in the United Kingdom. <s> Motocross can be dangerous and physically demanding.

title: Pharaoh's Island, River Thames
complex: Pharaoh's Island is an island in the River Thames, in Surrey, England, 270 m upstream of Shepperton Lock. <s> It was purchased by the Treasury to give to Admiral Nelson after the Battle of the Nile (1798). <s> He used it as a fishing retreat.
simple: Pharaoh's Island is an island on the River Thames, in Surrey, England. <s> The island is above Shepperton Lock. <s> The island was given to Admiral Nelson as a reward for winning Battle of the Nile, and he used it as a place to fish.

title: Dominique Strauss-Kahn
complex: Dominique Gaston André Strauss-Kahn (] ; born 25 April 1949) is a French politician, former managing director of the International Monetary Fund (IMF), and a controversial figure in the French Socialist Party due to his involvement in several financial and sexual scandals. <s> He is often referred to in the media, and by himself, by his initials DSK. <s> Strauss-Kahn was appointed managing director of the IMF on 28 September 2007, with the backing of his country's conservative president, Nicolas Sarkozy. <s> He served in that capacity until his resignation on 18 May 2011 in the wake of allegations that he had sexually assaulted a hotel maid. <s> He was a professor of economics at Paris West University Nanterre La Défense and Sciences Po, and was Minister of Economy and Finance from 1997 to 1999 as part of Lionel Jospin's "Plural Left" government. <s> He sought the nomination in the Socialist Party presidential primary of 2006, but was defeated by Ségolène Royal in November. <s> Strauss-Kahn resigned from the IMF on 18 May 2011, after being arrested by New York police on 15 May over allegations of sexual assault. <s> He was on a plane about to take off, when airport police asked that the plane be stopped; he was escorted off the plane and interviewed by police. <s> The case was later settled for an undisclosed amount. <s> Managing Director of the International Monetary Fund, 2007–2011 (resignation – sexual assault case) <s> On 14 May 2011, Nafissatou Diallo, a 32-year-old maid at the Sofitel New York Hotel, alleged that Strauss-Kahn had sexually assaulted her after she entered his suite. <s> After completing a lengthy investigation, prosecutors filed a motion to drop all charges against Strauss-Kahn, stating that they were not convinced of his culpability beyond a reasonable doubt due to serious issues in the complainant's credibility and inconclusive physical evidence, and therefore could not ask a jury to believe in it. <s> The motion was granted by Judge Obus in a hearing on August 23, 2011.
simple: Dominique Strauss-Kahn (born 25 April 1949) is a French politician and economist of Jewish descent. <s> In France, his name is usually abbreviated DSK. <s> He was nominated in the 2006 primary elections of his party to become a candidate for the French presidential election in 2007. <s> Ségolène Royal defeated him in these elections in November 2006. <s> On 18 May 2011 he resigned from his post at the IMF, in order to be able to focus on his defense. <s> He has held different posts in the French government, and was the head of the International Monetary Fund from 2007 to 2011. <s> On 14 May 2011, Strauss-Kahn was arrested and charged with sexually assaulting a woman in a hotel in New York. <s> Strauss-Kahn denies all charges.

title: Marcin Wrona
complex: Marcin Wrona (25 March 1973 – 19 September 2015) was a Polish film director. <s> His film "Demon" was shown at the 2015 Toronto International Film Festival. <s> He debuted at the TIFF in 2010, with "The Christening", and was also director of the Polish television series "Medics". <s> Wrona committed suicide by hanging in a hotel room on 19 September 2015 in Gdynia, while a film festival was taking place there. <s> The film "Demon" had been previously shown in Toronto and was shown in Gdynia.
simple: Marcin Wrona (25 March 1973 – 19 September 2015) was a Polish director and screenwriter. <s> His movies "The Christening" and "Demon" were both shown at the Toronto International Film Festival (TIFF) in 2010 and 2015, respectively. <s> Wrona was found dead hanging on 19 September 2015 at a hotel room in Gdynia.

title: Allan Warren
complex: Michael Allan Warren (born 26 October 1948) is an English portrait photographer, primarily known for his images of members of high society.
simple: Michael Allan Warren (born 26 October 1948 in Wimbledon, London) is an English society-photographer, writer, and former actor.

title: Giovanni Berlinguer
complex: Giovanni Berlinguer Cavaliere di Gran Croce OMRI (] ; 9 July 1924 – 6 April 2015) was an Italian politician, humanist and professor of social medicine. <s> He was born in Sassari, Sardinia, the son of Mario Berlinguer. <s> A physician and professor of public health, he worked first in social medicine at the University of Sassari (1969–1974) and then in occupational health at the University "La Sapienza" Rome (1975–1999). <s> Like his brother Enrico, Giovanni Berlinguer was a major figure in the Italian Communist Party (PCI) and was elected to the Chamber of Deputies in 1972, 1976 and 1979 and to the Senate in 1983 and 1987. <s> He ran for secretary of the Democrats of the Left (DS) in 2001, and was defeated by Piero Fassino 61.8% to 34.1%. <s> From 2004 to 2009 he was a Member of the European Parliament representing the DS and sits with the Party of European Socialists group. <s> At the convening of the Parliament on 20 July 2004 he was found to be the oldest member, and as such presided over the Parliament during the election of Josep Borrell Fontelles in 2004 and Hans-Gert Pöttering in 2007 as President of the Parliament. <s> He died in Rome at the age of 90.
simple: Giovanni Berlinguer (]), Cavaliere di Gran Croce OMRI, (9 July 1924 – 6 April 2015) was an Italian politician and Professor of Social Medicine. <s> He was born in Sassari, Sardinia, the son of Mario Berlinguer. <s> He ran for the secretarship of the Democrats of the Left (DS) in 2001, being defeated by Piero Fassino 61.8% to 34.1%. <s> From 2004 to 2009 he was a Member of the European Parliament representing the DS and sits with the Party of European Socialists group. <s> He died in Rome at the age of 90.

title: List of counties in Pennsylvania
complex: The following is a list of the sixty-seven counties of the U.S. state of Pennsylvania. <s> The city of Philadelphia is coterminous with Philadelphia County, the municipalities having been consolidated in 1854, and all remaining county government functions having been merged into the city after a 1951 referendum. <s> Eight of the ten most populous counties are in the southeastern portion of the state, including four out of the top five, and all of the top ten most populous counties are in either the Philadelphia or Pittsburgh Metropolitan Statistical Areas. <s> The Federal Information Processing Standard (FIPS) code, used by the United States government to uniquely identify counties, is provided with each entry. <s> FIPS codes are five-digit numbers; for Pennsylvania the codes start with 42 and are completed with the three-digit county code. <s> The FIPS code for each county in the table links to census data for that county.
simple: There are sixty-seven counties of the Commonwealth of Pennsylvania in the United States of America. <s> The city of Philadelphia shares boundaries with Philadelphia County, and governmental functions have been shared since 1854. <s> The Federal Information Processing Standard (FIPS) code, used by the United States government to uniquely identify counties, is provided with each entry. <s> FIPS codes are five digit numbers, for Pennsylvania the codes start with 42 and are completed with the three digit county code. <s> The FIPS code for each county in the table links to census data for that county.

title: Black Mirror
complex: Black Mirror is a British science fiction anthology television series created by Charlie Brooker. <s> He and Annabel Jones serve as the programme’s showrunners. <s> It examines modern society, particularly with regard to the unanticipated consequences of new technologies. <s> Episodes are standalone, usually set in an alternative present or the near future, often with a dark and satirical tone, although some are more experimental and lighter.
simple: Black Mirror is a British science fiction television series. <s> It was created by Charlie Brooker, who also writes the episodes. <s> The series mostly explores dystopian futures that could happen because of new technology, with a dark and satirical tone.

title: David Koch
complex: David Hamilton Koch ( ; May 3, 1940 – August 23, 2019) was an American businessman, philanthropist, political activist, and chemical engineer. <s> He joined the family business Koch Industries, the second-largest privately held company in the United States, in 1970. <s> He became president of the subsidiary Koch Engineering in 1979, and he became a co-owner of Koch Industries, with elder brother Charles, in 1983. <s> He served as an executive vice president until his retirement in 2018. <s> Upon retirement in June 2018 due to health issues, Koch received the title of director emeritus. <s> On June 5, 2018, the company announced his retirement from the company due to his declining health. <s> Koch died at his home in Southampton, New York, on August 23, 2019, at age 79.
simple: David Hamilton Koch (; May 3, 1940 – August 23, 2019) was an American businessman, philanthropist, political activist, and chemical engineer. <s> He joined the family business Koch Industries. <s> He became president of the subsidiary Koch Engineering in 1979. <s> He became a co-owner of Koch Industries, with older brother Charles, in 1983. <s> He was an executive vice president. <s> On June 5, 2018, the company announced his retirement from the company due to declining health issues. <s> Koch died at his Southampton, New York home from prostate cancer on August 23, 2019 at the age of 79.

title: Martin Nesbitt (politician)
complex: Martin Luther Nesbitt Jr. (September 25, 1946 – March 6, 2014) was a Democratic member of the North Carolina Senate. <s> He represented the 49th district (Buncombe County). <s> An attorney from Asheville, North Carolina, Nesbitt was elected to eleven terms in the state House before moving to the state senate in 2004. <s> He died in March 6, 2014, one week after being diagnosed with stomach cancer.
simple: Martin Luther Nesbitt, Jr. (September 25, 1946 – March 6, 2014) was an American Democratic member of the North Carolina Senate. <s> He represented the 49th district (Buncombe County). <s> Nesbitt died from stomach cancer on March 6, 2014 in his hometown of Asheville, North Carolina.

title: Rodrigo García (director)
complex: Rodrigo García Barcha (born 24 August 1959), more commonly known as Rodrigo García, is a Colombian television and film director, screenwriter and former cinematographer, best known for his films "Nine Lives" (2005), "Mother and Child" (2009), "Albert Nobbs" (2011), "Last Days in the Desert" (2015), as well as his work on the HBO drama series "In Treatment". <s> He also created, wrote, and directed the award-winning web series "Blue" (2012–2015), starring Julia Stiles, for which he won an IAWTV Award in 2014. <s> García was born in Bogotá, Colombia, the son of Colombian Nobel-winner writer Gabriel García Márquez and Mercedes Barcha Pardo. <s> Because of his father, he grew up around Carlos Fuentes, Julio Cortázar, Pablo Neruda and Luis Buñuel. <s> García has directed a variety of independent films, such as the award-winning "Nine Lives" (2005), which was nominated for the William Shatner Golden Groundhog Award for Best Underground Movie, and "Albert Nobbs" (2011), which screened at several film festivals, as well as episodes of several HBO series, including "Six Feet Under", "Carnivàle", and "Big Love". <s> He produced and developed the HBO drama series "In Treatment".
simple: Rodrigo García (born 24 August 1959) is a Colombian-born television and movie director and screenwriter. <s> He is the son of Nobel Prize-winning author Gabriel García Márquez. <s> Barcha was born in Bogotá, Colombia. <s> He directed movies and television series such as "Nine Lives" and "Albert Nobbs", and episodes of several HBO series, "Six Feet Under", "Carnivàle", and "Big Love".

title: Teresita de Castro
complex: Teresita "Tess" Leonardo-De Castro (born Teresita Jose Leonardo on October 10, 1948) was the 24th Chief Justice of the Supreme Court of the Philippines; appointed by President Rodrigo Duterte on August 28, 2018. <s> She assumed the vacated position since her predecessor, Maria Lourdes Sereno, was removed via a "quo warranto" petition (by declaring Sereno as a "de facto" chief justice and making her 2012 appointment as null and void "ab initio"); making De Castro the "de jure" 24th chief justice, making her the first female chief justice of the Supreme Court. <s> De Castro officially retired on October 10, 2018 after reaching the mandatory retirement age of 70; merely 46 days after serving as Chief Justice, surpassing the record of former Chief Justice Pedro Yap of being the shortest-tenured Chief Justice. <s> On August 25, 2018, President Duterte announced his appointment of Justice De Castro as the new Chief Justice of the Supreme Court, replacing Maria Lourdes Sereno who was removed from office by way of an 8–6 decision by the Supreme Court over a quo warranto petition. <s> She formally assumed the office on August 28.
simple: Teresita Leonardo-De Castro (born Teresita Jose Leonardo on October 8, 1948) was the 24th Chief Justice of the Supreme Court of the Philippines from August 25 to October 10, 2018. <s> After her retirement, she surpassed the record of former Chief Justice Pedro Yap of being the shortest tenured Chief Justice. <s> She replaced Maria Lourdes Sereno, who was removed from office.

title: North Bend, Ohio
complex: North Bend is a village in Miami Township, Hamilton County, Ohio, United States, along the Ohio River. <s> The population was 857 at the 2010 census.
simple: North Bend is a village in Miami Township, Hamilton County, Ohio, United States, along the Ohio River. <s> The population was 857 at the 2010 census.

title: Iraklis F.C. (Thessaloniki)
complex: Iraklis Football Club or Iraklis , is a Greek football club, based in the city of Thessaloniki, Macedonia, Greece. <s> The club currently competes in the Football League, the third tier of Greek football. <s> It plays its home matches at Kaftanzoglio Stadium. <s> Founded in 1908 as "Macedonikos Gymnasticos Syllogos" ("Macedonian Gymnastics Club"), they are one of the oldest in Greek football and the oldest in Thessaloniki, hence the nickname "Ghireos" (meaning "the Elder"). <s> A year later, the name "Iraklis" ("Heracles") was added to the club's name as an honour to the ancient Greek hero Heracles (or Hercules as the Roman equivalent). <s> The team's colours are cyan or blue and white, inspired by the Greek flag. <s> Iraklis is a founding member of "Macedonia Football Clubs Association", as well as the Hellenic Football Federation, as a part of G.S. Iraklis. <s> Before the formation of the nationwide league of Alpha Ethniki, Iraklis competed in the league that was run by the "Macedonia Football Clubs Association", winning it on no less than five occasions. <s> The club has also played in five Greek Cup finals, lifting the trophy once in the 1976 final, which is the club's only domestic trophy. <s> They have also an international title, as they won the Balkans Cup in 1985.
simple: Iraklis is a Greek football club which is based in Thessaloniki. <s> It is founded in 1908 and it is the most oldest club of Thessaloniki. <s> The name of club is the name of ancient Greek hero Hercules, which in Greek is said Iraklis. <s> Its colour is the blue and white. <s> It has won a Greek cup in 1976.

title: Bruce Lietzke
complex: Bruce Alan Lietzke (July 18, 1951 – July 28, 2018) was an American professional golfer who won 13 tournaments on the PGA Tour between 1977 and 1994, including two victories in the Canadian Open. <s> His best finish in a major championship was at the 1991 PGA Championship where he finished second, three strokes behind John Daly. <s> He had seven victories on the Champions Tour, including one senior major title, the 2003 U.S. Senior Open. <s> He played in the 1981 Ryder Cup. <s> Lietzke was born in Kansas City, Missouri. <s> He moved to Beaumont, Texas with his parents in 1960 and lived there until 1977, graduating from Forest Park High School in 1969. <s> In April 2017 Lietzke was diagnosed with an aggressive form of brain cancer called glioblastoma. <s> He died July 28, 2018 from complications of the disease and attempts at treating it, which his body rejected.
simple: Bruce Alan Lietzke (July 18, 1951 – July 28, 2018) was an American professional golfer. <s> He won 13 tournaments on the PGA Tour between 1977 and 1994, including two victories in the Canadian Open. <s> His best finish in a major championship was at the 1991 PGA Championship where he finished second behind John Daly. <s> He had seven victories on the Champions Tour. <s> He played in the 1981 Ryder Cup. <s> He was born in Kansas City, Missouri. <s> In April 2017 Lietzke was diagnosed with an aggressive form of brain cancer. <s> He died from the disease on July 28, 2018 in Athens, Texas, aged 67.

title: Bradford City A.F.C.
complex: Bradford City Association Football Club is a professional football club in Bradford, West Yorkshire, England. <s> The team compete in League Two, the fourth tier of the English football league system.
simple: Bradford City A.F.C. is an English football club. <s> They are based in Bradford, West Yorkshire.

title: Reply 1997
complex: Reply 1997 is a 2012 South Korean television series that centers on the lives of six friends in Busan, as the timeline moves back and forth between their past as 18-year-old high schoolers in 1997 and their present as 33-year-olds at their high school reunion dinner in 2012, where one couple will announce that they're getting married. <s> As the first installment of the "Reply" series, it also portrays the extreme fan culture that emerged in the 1990s when first generation idol groups such as H.O.T. and Sechs Kies took center stage and K-pop was just beginning to blossom. <s> The series originally aired live on cable channel tvN in 16 episodes (14 30-minute episodes aired back-to-back over a period of 7 weeks, with the last 2 episodes aired separately and lasting 1 hour each due to the amount of material the staff didn't want to edit out). <s> However, due to its popularity, the 15th and 16th episodes were also aired simultaneously on Mnet, OCN, O'live, Ongamenet and OnStyle. <s> Another series from the same writer and director, "Reply 1994" was produced in 2013. <s> Set in a college campus, it follows the pop culture events of that year, including the emergence of seminal K-pop group Seo Taiji and Boys and the basketball craze of the era.
simple: Reply 1997 (Hangul:응답하라 1997) is a Korean television series about two childhood friends, their friends, and family. <s> The story moves back and forth between their past high school lives in 1997 as 18-year-olds, and their present high school reunion in 2012. <s> It was aired on cable channel tvN from July 24 to September 18, 2012. <s> The success led to the production of its spin-off "Reply 1994", which was broadcast from October 18, 2013 on tvN.

title: First inauguration of Theodore Roosevelt
complex: The first inauguration of Theodore Roosevelt as the 26th President of the United States, took place on Saturday, September 14, 1901 at the Ansley Wilcox House, at 641 Delaware Avenue in Buffalo, New York, following the death of President William McKinley earlier that day. <s> The inauguration marked the commencement of the first term (a partial term of ) of Theodore Roosevelt as President. <s> John R. Hazel, U.S. District Judge for the Western District of New York, administered the Oath of office.
simple: The first inauguration of Theodore Roosevelt as the 26th President of the United States, took place on September 14, 1901 in Buffalo, New York. <s> John R. Hazel, U.S. District Judge for the Western District of New York, administered the oath of office.

title: Deimatic behaviour
complex: Spiders make use of a variety of different threat displays. <s> Some such as "Argiope" and "Pholcus" make themselves and their webs vibrate rapidly when they are disturbed; this blurs their outline and perhaps makes them look larger, as well as more difficult to locate precisely for an attack.
simple: Many animals have threat displays that make them look bigger.

title: Goodwater, Alabama
complex: Goodwater is a town in Coosa County, Alabama, United States. <s> At the 2010 census the population was 1,475. <s> It is part of the Talladega-Sylacauga Micropolitan Statistical Area. <s> As of the census of 2000, there were 1,633 people, 621 households, and 424 families residing in the city. <s> The population density was 249.6 people per square mile (96.4/km2).
simple: Goodwater is a city in Coosa County, Alabama, United States. <s> It is part of the Alexander City Micropolitan Statistical Area. <s> At the 2000 census the population was 1,633.

title: Škoda Auto
complex: ŠKODA AUTO (] ), more commonly known as Škoda, is a Czech automobile manufacturer founded in 1895 as Laurin & Klement. <s> Its headquarters are in Mladá Boleslav, Czech Republic. <s> In 1925 Laurin & Klement was acquired by the industrial conglomerate Škoda Works, which itself became state owned in 1948. <s> After 1991 it was gradually privatized and in 2000 Škoda became a wholly owned subsidiary of the Volkswagen Group. <s> The Škoda Works were established as an arms manufacturer in 1859. <s> ŠKODA AUTO (and its predecessors) is one of the five oldest companies producing cars and has an unbroken history alongside Daimler, Opel, Peugeot and Tatra. <s> As with many long-established car manufacturers, the company which would become Škoda Auto started in the early 1890s by manufacturing bicycles. <s> Škoda (then Laurin & Klement) factories were founded in 1896 as a velocipede manufacturer. <s> In 1894 (1894) , 26-year-old Václav Klement, who was a bookseller in Mladá Boleslav, Kingdom of Bohemia (today's Czech Republic, then part of Austria-Hungary), was unable to obtain spare parts to repair his German bicycle. <s> Klement returned his bicycle to the manufacturers, Seidel and Naumann, with a letter, in Czech, asking them to carry out repairs, only to receive a reply, in German, stating: "If you want us to answer you, we insist that you convey your message in a language we understand." <s> Not satisfied with the reply and realising the business potential, Klement, despite having no technical experience, decided to start a bicycle repair shop, which he and Václav Laurin opened in 1896 in Mladá Boleslav. <s> Before going into partnership with Klement, Laurin was an established bicycle manufacturer in the nearby town of Turnov. <s> In 1898, after moving to their newly built factory, the pair bought a Werner "Motocyclette". <s> Laurin & Klement's first motorcyclette, powered by an engine mounted on the handlebars driving the front wheels, proved dangerous and unreliable — an early accident on it cost Laurin a front tooth. <s> To design a safer machine with its structure around the engine, the pair wrote to German ignition specialist Robert Bosch for advice on a different electromagnetic system. <s> Their new "Slavia" motorcycle made its debut in 1899 and the company became the first motorcycle factory in Central Europe. <s> In 1900, with a company workforce of 32, Slavia exports began and 150 machines were shipped to London for the Hewtson firm. <s> Shortly afterwards, the press credited them as makers of the first motorcycle. <s> By 1905, the firm was manufacturing automobiles, making it the second-oldest car manufacturer in the Czech lands after Tatra. <s> The company, with an area of 7800 m2 , had a workforce of 320 and used 170 special machine-tools, power-driven by 100 hp of steam power. <s> The first model, Voiturette A, was a success and the company was established both within Austria-Hungary and internationally. <s> After World War I the Laurin & Klement company began producing trucks, but in 1924, after running into problems and being affected by a fire on their premises, the company sought a new partner. <s> Meanwhile, ""Akciová společnost, dříve Škodovy závody"" (Limited Company, formerly the Škoda Works), an arms manufacturer and multi-sector concern in Pilsen which had become one of the largest industrial enterprises in Europe and the largest in Czechoslovakia, sought to enlarge its non-arms manufacturing base and acquired Laurin & Klement in 1925. <s> It also started manufacturing cars in cooperation with Hispano-Suiza. <s> Most of the later production took place under Škoda's name. <s> An assembly line was used for production from 1930 onwards. <s> In the same year a formal spin-off of the car manufacture into a new company, "Akciová společnost pro automobilový průmysl" or abbreviated "ASAP", took place. <s> ASAP remained a wholly owned subsidiary of the Škoda Works and continued to sell cars under the Škoda marque. <s> Apart from the factory in Mladá Boleslav it included also the firm's representation, sales offices and services, as well as a central workshop in Prague. <s> At the time, the car factory in Mladá Boleslav covered an area of 215,000 square metres and employed 3,750 blue-collar and 500 white-collar workers. <s> After a decline caused by the economic depression, Škoda introduced a new line of cars in the 1930s which significantly differed from its previous products. <s> A new design of chassis with backbone tube and all-around independent suspension was developed under the leadership of chief engineer Vladimír Matouš and modelled on the one first introduced by Hans Ledwinka in Tatra. <s> First used on model Škoda 420 Standard in 1933, it aimed at solving insufficient torsional stiffness of the ladder frame. <s> During the occupation of Czechoslovakia in World War II the Škoda Works were turned into part of the "Reichswerke Hermann Göring" serving the German war effort by producing components for military terrain vehicles, military planes, other weapon components and cartridge cases. <s> Vehicle output decreased from 7,052 in 1939 to 683 in 1944, of which only 35 were passenger cars. <s> A total of 316 trucks were produced between January and May 1945. <s> The UK and US air forces bombed the Škoda works repeatedly between 1940 and 1945. <s> The final massive air raid took place on 25 April 1945 and resulted in almost the complete destruction of the Škoda armament works and about 1,000 dead or injured. <s> In 2017 Auto Shanghai, Škoda displayed its Vision E concept for an all-electric 300bhp coupé-SUV, with level 3 autonomy capability and 500 km range. <s> It is based on the VW MEB platform and Škoda Auto will also manufacture electric-vehicle batteries for the Volkswagen Group in its facility in the Czech Republic. <s> The second development stage, the Škoda Vision iV was revealed in March 2019 and is planned to be on sale from the second half of 2020.
simple: Škoda Auto (]), better known as Škoda, is an automobile maker. <s> Škoda was bought by the Volkswagen Group in 2000. <s> Škoda Works was started as a firearms maker in 1859. <s> Škoda Auto goes back to the early 1890s as a company which started out making bicycles. <s> In 1894, 26-year old Václav Klement (a bookseller in Mladá Boleslav) could not find any spare parts to fix his bicycle. <s> Klement returned his bicycle to the makers, Seidel and Naumann, with a letter. <s> The letter asked the company to repair the bicycle. <s> Even though he did not have any experience, he decided to start a bicycle repair shop. <s> He and Václav Laurin opened this in 1895 in Mladá Boleslav. <s> Before working with Klement, Laurin was a bicycle maker in the town of Turnov. <s> In 1898, after moving to their newly-built factory, the pair bought a Werner "motorcyclist". <s> Laurin & Klement's first motorcyclette was powered by an engine on the handlebars. <s> It was dangerous and unreliable. <s> Laurin had an accident on it, and lost one of his front teeth. <s> To design a safer motorcycle, the pair wrote to German specialist Robert Bosch for advice. <s> The pair's new motorcycle went on sale in 1899. <s> In 1900, when the company had 32 people working for them, motorcycles began being exported. <s> 150 machines were shipped to London. <s> Shortly after, the press said that they were the makers of the first motorcycle. <s> By 1905 the company was making automobiles. <s> The first model, Voiturette A, was a success. <s> The company was set up both within Austria-Hungary and all over the world. <s> After World War I, the Laurin-Klement company began making trucks. <s> However, in 1924, the company looked for a partner after running into problems. <s> Most things made later were under the Škoda name. <s> Škoda was successful again after an economic depression. <s> During World War II, when Nazi Germany had invaded Czechoslovakia, the Škoda works was turned into part of "Reichswerke Hermann Göring". <s> It is based in the Czech Republic.

title: Enrique Agudo
complex: Enrique Agudo Camacho (born 1 January 1967 in Tarragona) is a class 10 table tennis player from Spain. <s> He played table tennis at the 1996, 2000 and 2004 Summer Paralympics. <s> In 1996, he finished third in the men's class 10 singles event. <s> In 2000, he finished third in the class 10 doubles event.
simple: Enrique Agudo Camacho (born January 1, 1967 in Tarragona) is a table tennis athlete from Spain. <s> He played table tennis at the 1996 Summer Paralympics, 2000 Summer Paralympics and 2004 Summer Paralympics. <s> In 1996, he finished third in the men's Class 10 singles event. <s> In 2000, he finished third in the Class 10 doubles event.

title: Lint, Belgium
complex: Lint (] ) is a municipality located in the Belgian province of Antwerp. <s> The municipality only comprises the town of Lint proper.
simple: Lint is a municipality in the Belgian province of Antwerp.

title: Classical mechanics
complex: Classical mechanics describes the motion of macroscopic objects, from projectiles to parts of machinery, and astronomical objects, such as spacecraft, planets, stars and galaxies. <s> If the present state of an object is known it is possible to predict by the laws of classical mechanics how it will move in the future (determinism) and how it has moved in the past (reversibility). <s> Classical mechanics uses common-sense notions of how matter and forces exist and interact. <s> It assumes that matter and energy have definite, knowable attributes such as location in space and speed. <s> Non-relativistic mechanics also assumes that forces act instantaneously (see also Action at a distance). <s> Acceleration represents the velocity's change over time. <s> Velocity can change in either magnitude or direction, or both. <s> Occasionally, a decrease in the magnitude of velocity ""v"" is referred to as "deceleration", but generally any change in the velocity over time, including deceleration, is simply referred to as acceleration. <s> The quantity "m"v is called the (canonical) momentum. <s> The net force on a particle is thus equal to the rate of change of the momentum of the particle with time. <s> Newton founded his principles of natural philosophy on three proposed laws of motion: the law of inertia, his second law of acceleration (mentioned above), and the law of action and reaction; and hence laid the foundations for classical mechanics. <s> Both Newton's second and third laws were given the proper scientific and mathematical treatment in Newton's "Philosophiæ Naturalis Principia Mathematica."
simple: Classical mechanics is the part of physics that describes how everyday things move and how their motion changes because of forces. <s> If we know how things are moving now, classical mechanics allows us to predict how they will move in the future and how they were moving in the past. <s> We can use classical mechanics to predict how things like planets and rockets move. <s> Classical mechanics is used most of the time for most of the things we can see, and that are not moving too fast. <s> Then we need to use quantum mechanics. <s> How fast the velocity changes is called the acceleration. <s> Another way of saying this is that the net force on an object equals the rate of change of its momentum. <s> Newton's three laws of motion are important to classical mechanics.

title: Essonne
complex: Essonne (] ) is a French department in the region of Île-de-France. <s> It is named after the Essonne River.
simple: Essonne is a department to the south of Paris in the Île-de-France region.

title: Gansu
complex: Gansu (; formerly romanized as Kansu) is a landlocked province in Northwest China. <s> Its capital and largest city is Lanzhou, located in the southeast part of the province. <s> Gansu has an area of 454000 km2 , and the vast majority of its land is more than 1000 m above sea level. <s> It lies between the Tibetan Plateau and the Loess Plateau, bordering Mongolia (Govi-Altai Province) to the northwest, Inner Mongolia and Ningxia to the north, Shaanxi to the east, Sichuan to the south, and Xinjiang to the west. <s> The Yellow River passes through the southern part of the province. <s> The province contains the geographical centre of China, marked by the Center of the Country Monument at . <s> Part of the Gobi Desert is located in Gansu, as well as small parts of the Badain Jaran Desert and the Tengger Desert. <s> The landscape in Gansu is very mountainous in the south and flat in the north. <s> The mountains in the south are part of the Qilian Mountains, while the far western Altyn-Tagh contains the province's highest point, at 5830 m . <s> Gansu generally has a semi-arid to arid continental climate (Köppen "BSk" or "BWk") with warm to hot summers and cold to very cold winters, although diurnal temperature ranges are often so large that maxima remain above 0 C even in winter. <s> However, due to extreme altitude, some areas of Gansu exhibit a subarctic climate ("Dwc") – with winter temperatures sometimes dropping to -40 C .
simple: Gansu is a province of the People's Republic of China. <s> The capital is Lanzhou, in the southeast part of the province. <s> It has an area of 454,430 km2. <s> It contains the geographical centre of China. <s> The Gobi Desert lies partly in Gansu, and the Yellow River flows in the south. <s> The province is mountainous in the south but flat in the north. <s> Gansu Province has a dry continental climate with cold winters and hot summers.

title: Jean-Paul L'Allier
complex: Jean-Paul L'Allier (August 12, 1938 – January 5, 2016) was a Quebec politician, a two-term Member of the National Assembly of Quebec (MNA) and the 38th mayor of Quebec City. <s> L'Allier was born in Hudson, Montérégie in 1938 and received a law degree from the University of Ottawa. <s> He practised law in the Ottawa and Outaouais regions in the 1960s. <s> He worked for the Montreal newspaper Le Devoir in the 1980s. <s> He was a self-proclaimed Liberal, sovereigntist and social democrat.
simple: Jean-Paul L'Allier (August 12, 1938 – January 5, 2016) was a Canadian politician and journalist. <s> He served as the 38th Mayor of Quebec City from 1989 to 2005. <s> L'Allier died after an illness on January 5, 2016 in Quebec City. <s> He was born in Hudson, Quebec. <s> He also worked for the Montreal newspaper "Le Devoir" in the 1980s.

title: Pilot Point, Alaska
complex: Pilot Point (Alutiiq: "Agisaq") is a city in Lake and Peninsula Borough, Alaska, United States, on the Alaska Peninsula. <s> As of the 2010 census, the population of the city was 68, down from 100 in 2000. <s> Pilot Point is located at (57.560226, -157.582267). <s> Most of the community (village) is located on a high, ancient glacial moraine which abuts the eastern shore of Ugashik Bay six nautical miles upstream from Smoky Point and eighteen nautical miles (33 km) downstream from the village of Ugashik.
simple: Pilot Point is a city in Alaska. <s> Pilot Point is at (57.560226, -157.582267).

title: Pybba of Mercia
complex: –606/615) (also Pibba, Wibba, or Wybba) was an early King of Mercia. <s> He was the son of Creoda and father of Penda and Eowa. <s> Unusually, the names Pybba and Penda are likely of British Celtic, rather than Germanic, origin. <s> His dates are sometimes given in genealogies as birth in 570, the beginning of his reign in 593, and death in either 606 or 615, but with no apparent evidence; the "Anglo-Saxon Chronicle" just mentions him as father of Penda, with no further detail. <s> Besides Penda and Eowa (who the author of the "Historia Brittonum" said were the sons of Pybba who were the best known to him), Pybba also apparently had a son named Coenwalh. <s> Every king from Penda until Ceolwulf, who was deposed in 823, was said to be a descendant of Pybba, either through Penda, Eowa, or Coenwalh (perhaps excluding Beornrad, who ruled briefly and whose background is unknown). <s> Pybba also is said to have had a daughter. <s> Though unnamed, she was possibly the first wife of Cenwalh, King of Wessex (648–674).
simple: Pybba ( 606) (also Pibba or Wibba) was an early Anglian King of Mercia. <s> He was the father of kings Penda and Eowa. <s> Pybba was the son of Creoda. <s> The probable dates of his reign are from 593– 606. <s> The Mercian kings down to Ceolwulf all claimed to be descendants of Pybba. <s> He also had a daughter who married (as his first wife) Cenwalh of Wessex Pybba either died or was deposed in 606.

title: List of colonial governors of Sierra Leone
complex: This is a list of colonial administrators in Sierra Leone from the establishment of the Province of Freedom by the Committee for the Relief of the Black Poor in 1787 until Sierra Leone's independence in 1961. <s> On 14 May 1787, the Province of Freedom was founded by the Committee for the Relief of the Black Poor for freed slaves. <s> On 22 August 1788, the Province of Freedom and land along the Freetown peninsula was granted to Captain John Taylor of . <s> In 1789, it was abandoned. <s> In January 1791, the Granville Town was restored by the St. George Bay Company. <s> In 1792, Freetown was founded as the main town of the newly established Colony of Sierra Leone <s> On 5 July 1799, the Province of Freedom was renamed Sierra Leone. <s> On 1 January 1808, Sierra Leone (including coastal area) becomes Crown colony of the United Kingdom, and Sierra Leone Company rule was ended. <s> On 17 October 1821, Sierra Leone territory becomes part of British West African Territories. <s> Its Governorship was held simultaneously by Governor (from 1827 until 1837 Lieutenant governor) of Sierra Leone. <s> On 13 January 1850, the British West African Territories was dissolved and Sierra Leone again becomes a separate crown colony. <s> On 19 February 1866, Sierra Leone territory becomes part of the British West African Settlements. <s> Its Governorship was held simultaneously by Governor of Sierra Leone. <s> On 17 December 1874, British West African Settlements was renamed British West Africa Settlements. <s> On 28 November 1888, the British West Africa Settlements was dissolved and Sierra Leone again becomes a separate crown colony <s> On 24 August 1895, hinterland of Sierra Leone becomes British protectorate, and crown colony was renamed Sierra Leone Colony and Protectorate. <s> In 1961, Sierra Leone achieved independence from the United Kingdom. <s> After independence, the viceroy in Sierra Leone was the Governor-General of Sierra Leone.
simple: This is a list of colonial administrators in Sierra Leone from the establishment of the Province of Freedom by the Committee for the Relief of the Black Poor in 1787 until Sierra Leone's independence in 1961. <s> On 14 May 1787, the Province of Freedom was founded by the Committee for the Relief of the Black Poor for freed slaves. <s> On 22 August 1788, the Province of Freedom and the land along the Freetown peninsula was given to Captain John Taylor of the HMS "Miro". <s> In 1789, it was abandoned. <s> In January 1791, Granville Town was taken back by the St. George Bay Company. <s> In 1792, Freetown was founded as the main town of the newly established Colony of Sierra Leone <s> On 5 July 1799, the Province of Freedom was renamed Sierra Leone. <s> On 1 January 1808, Sierra Leone (including the coastal area) becomes a Crown colony of the United Kingdom, and the Sierra Leone Company stopped being in charge. <s> On 17 October 1821, Sierra Leone territory became part of British West African Territories. <s> Its Governorship was held by the Governor (from 1827 until 1837 Lieutenant governor) of Sierra Leone. <s> On 13 January 1850, Sierra Leone becomes a separate crown colony again. <s> On 19 February 1866, Sierra Leone territory becomes part of the British West African Settlements. <s> Its Governorship was held by the Governor of Sierra Leone. <s> On 17 December 1874, British West African Settlements became known as British West Africa Settlements. <s> On 28 November 1888, the Sierra Leone became a separate crown colony again. <s> On 24 August 1895, the land by the coast of Sierra Leone became a British protectorate, and the crown colony was renamed as the Sierra Leone Colony and Protectorate. <s> In 1961, Sierra Leone achieved independence from the United Kingdom. <s> After independence, the viceroy in Sierra Leone was the Governor-General of Sierra Leone.

title: Requeil
complex: Requeil is a commune in the Sarthe department in the region of Pays-de-la-Loire in north-western France.
simple: Requeil is a commune. <s> It is found in the region Pays de la Loire in the Sarthe department in the west of France.

title: Le Petit-Abergement
complex: Le Petit-Abergement is a former commune in the Ain department in eastern France. <s> On 1 January 2016, it was merged into the new commune Haut-Valromey.
simple: Le Petit-Abergement is a former commune in the Ain department in eastern France. <s> On 1 January 2016, it was merged into the new commune Haut-Valromey.

title: Ron Bass (wrestler)
complex: Ronald Heard (December 21, 1948 – March 7, 2017) was an American professional wrestler, best known under the name "The Outlaw" Ron Bass. <s> His gimmick was a Texan cowboy who entered World Wrestling Federation (WWF) rings to the sound of a bullwhip. <s> In March 2017, Heard was hospitalized due to a burst appendix. <s> He died on March 7 at the age of 68 due to complications following surgery.
simple: Ronald Heard (December 21, 1948 – March 7, 2017) was a former American professional wrestler. <s> He was best known under the name "The Outlaw" Ron Bass. <s> His gimmick was a Texan cowboy who entered World Wrestling Federation (WWF) rings to the sound of a bullwhip. <s> In March 2017, Bass was hospitalized in Tampa, Florida due to a burst appendix and underwent surgery. <s> He died on March 7, 2017 from complications of appendicitis-related surgery at the age of 68.

title: Houbara bustard
complex: The houbara bustard ("Chlamydotis undulata"), also known as African houbara, is a large bustard native to North Africa, Canary Islands and southwestern Asia, where it lives in arid habitats. <s> It is dull brown with black markings on the wings, a greyish neck and a black ruff along the side of the neck.
simple: The Houbara Bustard, Chlamydotis undulata, is a large bird in the bustard family.

title: Mansigné
complex: Mansigné is a commune in the Sarthe department in the region of Pays-de-la-Loire in north-western France.
simple: Mansigné is a commune. <s> It is found in the region Pays de la Loire in the Sarthe department in the west of France.

title: Burley Park railway station
complex: Burley Park railway station in Leeds, West Yorkshire, England, is the first stop on the Harrogate Line, 2.25 mi north west of Leeds railway station towards Harrogate and York. <s> The station was opened on 28 November 1988 by British Rail.
simple: Burley Park railway station is a railway station in the Burley area of Leeds, West Yorkshire. <s> It is one stop away from Leeds City Station on the line between Leeds City Centre and Harrogate.

title: John Jenkins (composer)
complex: John Jenkins (1592–1678), English composer, was born in Maidstone, Kent, and died at Kimberley, Norfolk. <s> After the Restoration he obtained a place as a musician to the Royal Court. <s> However, the viol consort was less fashionable in the court of Charles II.
simple: John Jenkins (1592–1678) was an English composer. <s> After the Restoration he was appointed as a court musician.

title: Tiffany (name)
complex: Tiffany is an English form of the Greek Theophania. <s> It was formerly often given to children born on the feast of Theophania, that is, Epiphany. <s> The equivalent Greek male name is Theophanes (Θεοφάνης), commonly shortened to Phanis (Φάνης) and the female is Theophania (Θεοφανία) or Theophano (Θεοφανώ), colloquially Phani (Φανή).
simple: The name is English for the Greek name "Theophania". <s> "Tiffany" was formerly given to children who were born near Epiphany.

title: Cheignieu-la-Balme
complex: Cheignieu-la-Balme is a commune in the Ain department in eastern France.
simple: Cheignieu-la-Balme is a commune.

title: Jet (lignite)
complex: Jet is a type of lignite, a precursor to coal, and is a gemstone. <s> Jet is not a mineral, but rather a mineraloid. <s> It has an organic origin, being derived from wood that has decayed under extreme pressure. <s> The English noun "jet" derives from the French word for the same material, "jaiet" (modern French "jais"), ultimately referring to the ancient town of Gagae. <s> Jet is either black or dark brown, but may contain pyrite inclusions, which are of brassy colour and metallic lustre. <s> The adjective "jet-black", meaning as dark a black as possible, derives from this material.
simple: Therefore, jet was not called a mineral, but instead a "mineraloid". <s> The English noun "jet" comes from the French word for the same material: "jaiet". <s> Jet is either black or dark brown, but may contain pyrite inclusions, which are of brassy colour and metallic lustre. <s> The adjective "jet-black", meaning as dark a black as possible, comes from this material.

title: List of Baptists
complex: This list of Baptists covers those who were members of Baptist churches or raised in Baptist churches. <s> It does not imply that all who appear on the list were practicing Baptists or remained Baptists all their lives.
simple: This is a list of Baptists.

title: Fulda
complex: Fulda (] ) (historically in English called Fuld) is a city in Hesse, Germany; it is located on the river Fulda and is the administrative seat of the Fulda district ("Kreis"). <s> In 1990, the town hosted the 30th Hessentag state festival. <s> In 744 Saint Sturm, a disciple of Saint Boniface, founded the Benedictine monastery of Fulda as one of Boniface's outposts in the reorganization of the church in Germany. <s> It later served as a base from which missionaries could accompany Charlemagne's armies in their political and military campaigns to fully conquer and convert pagan Saxony. <s> The foundation of the abbey Fulda and its territory originated with an Imperial grant, and the sovereign principality therefore was subject only to the German emperor. <s> Fulda became a bishopric in 1752 and the prince-abbots were given the additional title of prince-bishop. <s> The prince-abbots (and later prince-bishops) ruled Fulda and the surrounding region until the bishopric was forcibly dissolved by Napoleon I in 1802. <s> The city went through a baroque building campaign in the 18th century, resulting in the current “Baroque City” status. <s> This included a remodeling of Fulda Cathedral (1704–12) and of the "Stadtschloss "(Fulda Castle-Palace, 1707–12) by Johann Dientzenhofer. <s> The city parish church, St. Blasius, was built between 1771–85. <s> In 1764 a porcelain factory was started in Fulda under Prince-Bishop, Prince-Abbot Heinrich von Bibra, but shortly after his death it was closed down in 1789 by his successor, Prince-Bishop, Prince-Abbot Adalbert von Harstall.
simple: Fulda (]) is a city in Hesse, Germany; it is on the Fulda River and is the administrative seat of the Fulda district ("Kreis"). <s> The Benedictine monastery of Fulda was founded in 744 by Saint Sturm, a disciple of Saint Boniface, when Boniface was reorganising the church in Germany. <s> From its foundation, the abbey Fulda and its territory was subject only to the German emperor, not to the control of the local lords. <s> Fulda was made a bishopric in 1752 and the prince-abbots were given the additional title of prince-bishop. <s> The prince-abbots (and later prince-bishops) ruled Fulda and the surrounding region until the bishopric was forcibly dissolved by Napoleon in 1802. <s> From 1764 until 1789 Fulda had a porcelain factory. <s> The factory was begun under Prince-Bishop, Prince-Abbot Heinrich von Bibra and closed down shortly after his death by his successor, Prince-Bishop, Prince-Abbot Adalbert von Harstall.

title: Eugene Levy
complex: Eugene Levy, (born December 17, 1946) is a Canadian actor, comedian, producer, director, and writer. <s> He is the only actor to have appeared in all eight of the "American Pie" films, in his role as Noah Levenstein. <s> He often plays flustered and unconventional figures, with his humour often deriving from his excessive explanations of matters and the way in which he deals with sticky situations. <s> Levy is a regular collaborator of actor-director Christopher Guest, appearing in and co-writing four of his films, commencing with "Waiting for Guffman" (1996). <s> Levy was born to a Jewish family in Hamilton, Ontario. <s> His mother was a homemaker and his father was a foreman at an automobile plant. <s> He went to Westdale Secondary School, and attended McMaster University. <s> He was vice-president of the McMaster Film Board, a student film group, where he met moviemaker Ivan Reitman. <s> Levy married Deborah Divine in 1977 and together have two children: Dan and Sarah.
simple: Eugene Levy, (born December 17, 1946) is a Canadian movie, television, stage, voice actor, and comedian. <s> He is known for his role in the all eight of the "American Pie" series of movies. <s> Levy was born in Hamilton, Ontario, Canada on December 17, 1946. <s> and studied at McMaster University. <s> He has been married to Deborah Divine since 1977.

title: Nagham Nawzat
complex: Nagham Nawzat Hasan (Arabic: نغم نوزات حسن, born 1978) is an Iraqi Yazidi Doctor who was given an International Women of Courage Award in 2016.
simple: Nagham Nawzat Hasan (Arabic: نغم نوزات حسن ) or Nagham Nawzat is a doctor from Iraq. <s> In 2015 she received the International Women of Courage Award. <s> Nagham Nawzat Hasan is a Kurdish Yazidi gynecologist.

title: Étroussat
complex: Étroussat is a commune in the Allier department in central France.
simple: Étroussat is a commune. <s> It is found in the Allier department in the center of France.

title: Derealization
complex: Derealization (sometimes abbreviated as DR) is an alteration in the perception or experience of the external world so that it seems unreal. <s> Other symptoms include feeling as though one's environment is lacking in spontaneity, emotional coloring, and depth. <s> It is a dissociative symptom of many conditions. <s> Derealization is a subjective experience of unreality of the outside world, while depersonalization is sense of unreality in one's personal self, although most authors currently do not regard derealization (surroundings) and depersonalization (self) as separate constructs.
simple: Derealization (DR) is a change in the way someone views the world so that it seems unreal. <s> Similar to derealization is depersonalization, but the two are different. <s> Depersonalization is a sense of unreality about oneself. <s> Derealization is a sense of unreality of the outside world.

title: Channel 5 (UK)
complex: Channel 5 is a British free-to-air television network. <s> It was launched in 1997, and was the fifth national terrestrial analogue network in the United Kingdom. <s> Channel 5 HD is a high-definition simulcast of Channel 5. <s> The channel launched on Sky channel 171 and Virgin Media channel 150 on 13 July 2010. <s> In Summer 2015, Channel 5 and Channel 5 HD switched places, with Channel 5 HD now being located in Channel 5's original space of channel 105.
simple: Channel 5 is a television channel which broadcasts to the United Kingdom. <s> It started on 30 March 1997. <s> On 13 July 2010 Channel 5 started a High Definition version of their channel on Sky and Virgin Media.

title: North Korea at the 2018 Winter Paralympics
complex: North Korea was one the competing teams in 2018 Winter Paralympics in Pyeongchang, South Korea. <s> The Games were the first for North Korea for the Winter Paralympics. <s> The country has two skiers, Kim Jong-hyon and Ma Yu-chol, racing in para-Nordic skiing. <s> The International Paralympic Committee said North Korea was going to participate in the Winter Games for the first time. <s> North Korea will participate under a Korean Unification Flag like their delegation for the 2018 Winter Olympics did, in the Women's Ice Hockey tournament. <s> However, North Korea athletes marched in the Paralympics opening ceremony under its own flag, unlike the Olympics opening ceremony where they marched under the Korean unification flag alongside with South Korean athletes. <s> North Korea had previously participated at the 2012 and 2016 Summer Paralympics. <s> Two athletes represented North Korea at the 2018 Winter Paralympics. <s> They were Kim Jong-hyon and Ma Yu-chol and both competed in para-Nordic skiing. <s> The two athletes Kim Jong-hyon and Ma Yu-chol first competed internationally at the 2018 Paralympic Nordic Skiing World Cup, in Oberried, Germany in January 2018. <s> Kim was 59th in the world in January 2018 in the sitting cross country skiing men's race with 516.18 points. <s> Ma was 58th in the world in January 2018 in the sitting cross country skiing men's race with 505.88 points.
simple: North Korea sent people to compete at the 2018 Winter Paralympics in Pyeongchang, South Korea. <s> It was the first time that North Korea competed in the Winter Paralympics. <s> This is the first time that North Korea went to the Winter Paralympics. <s> The country had two skiers, Kim Jonghyon and Ma Yuchol, racing in para-Nordic skiing. <s> The International Paralympic Committee (IPC) said North Korea was going to participate in the Winter Games for the first time. <s> The North Koreans will competing under a Korean unification flag like their delegation for the 2018 Winter Olympics did. <s> The country had gone to the 2012 Summer Paralympics and the 2016 Summer Paralympics. <s> Two people are representing North Korea at the 2018 Winter Paralympics. <s> They are Kim Jonghyon and Ma Yuchol. <s> They are Kim Jonghyon and Ma Yuchol. <s> They first competed internationally at the 2018 Paralympic Nordic Skiing World Cup in Oberried, Germany in January 2018. <s> Kim was number 59 in the world in January 2018 in cross country skiing men's sitting race. <s> He had 516.18 points. <s> Ma was number 58 in the world in January 2018 in cross country skiing men's sitting race. <s> He had 505.88 points.

title: East Coast (train operating company)
complex: East Coast, the trading name of the East Coast Main Line Company, was a British train operating company running the InterCity East Coast franchise on the East Coast Main Line between London, Yorkshire, North East England, and Scotland. <s> East Coast ran long-distance inter-city services from its Central London terminus at on two primary routes; the first to Leeds and the second to Edinburgh via Newcastle with other services reaching into Yorkshire and Northern and Central Scotland. <s> It commenced operations on 14 November 2009 and ceased on 28 February 2015. <s> In January 2014, FirstGroup, Keolis/Eurostar and Stagecoach/Virgin were announced as the shortlisted bidders for the new franchise. <s> The franchise passed to Virgin Trains East Coast on 1 March 2015. <s> East Coast paid back over £1 billion to the government over the course of its franchise.
simple: East Coast was a government-owned British train operating company. <s> It ran high-speed passenger trains on the East Coast Main Line between London, Yorkshire, the North East and Scotland, being forced to take over after National Express East Coast defaulted on their franchise. <s> It started operations on 14 November 2009. <s> It ended operations on 28 February 2015. <s> The franchise was re-let to Virgin Trains East Coast, ending the period of government ownership, despite contributing a lot of money to the Treasury and calls for the government to retain the franchise. <s> East Coast paid back over £1 billion to the government over the course of its franchise, more than twice as much as rival Virgin Trains did in the same time period on the West Coast Main Line. <s> East Coast’s successor, Virgin Trains East Coast pays much more money back to the government than East Coast did: £3.3 billion over 8 years, compared to East Coast’s £1 billion.

title: Yekaterina Gamova
complex: Yekaterina Aleksandrovna Gamova ( ; born 17 October 1980) is a retired Russian volleyball player. <s> She was a member of the national team that won the gold medals at the 2006 and 2010 FIVB Volleyball Women's World Championships, and the silver medal in both the Athens 2004 and Sydney 2000 Olympic Games. <s> She is 2.06 m tall with EU size 49 feet, making her one of the tallest female athletes in the world Her role was outside hitter/opposite.
simple: Yekaterina Aleksandrovna Gamova (; born 17 October 1980) is a Russian volleyball player. <s> She was a member of the Russian team that won the gold medals at the FIVB Volleyball World Championships in 2006 and 2010. <s> She was also a member of the Russian team that won silver medals in both the Athens 2004 and Sydney 2000 Olympic Games. <s> Gamova is 2.02 m tall with an EU shoe size of 49. <s> This makes her one of the tallest female athletes in the world. <s> Her role is outside hitter/opposite.

title: Susan Collins
complex: Susan Margaret Collins (born December 7, 1952) is an American politician serving as the senior United States Senator for Maine. <s> A Republican, Collins has served in the Senate since 1997. <s> Collins was first elected to the U.S. Senate in 1996. <s> She was re-elected in 2002, 2008, and 2014.
simple: Susan Margaret Collins is a Senator of the United States from Maine. <s> The Senator was born December 7, 1952. <s> Collins was elected to the Senate in 1996.

title: Pradikta Wicaksono
complex: Pradikta Wicaksono (born January 10, 1986) or often called Dikta, is an Indonesian singer. <s> He is a singer for the group Yovie & Nuno, along with Dudi Oris. <s> He joined Yovie & Nuno in 2007. <s> he had sung many of the famous songs like The Special One, Still the One and many more... <s> Pradikta Wicaksono was born in Jakarta, Indonesia, on January 10, 1986. <s> He was the second child of three siblings.

title: Donna Shalala
complex: Donna Edna Shalala ( ; born February 14, 1941) is an American politician and academic serving as the U.S. Representative for Florida 's congressional district since 2019. <s> A member of the Democratic Party, she previously served as the 18th United States Secretary of Health and Human Services under President Bill Clinton from 1993 to 2001. <s> Shalala served as President of the University of Miami, a private university in Coral Gables, Florida, from 2001 through 2015. <s> Previously she was the President of Hunter College from 1980 until 1988 and chancellor of the University of Wisconsin–Madison from 1988 to 1993. <s> Shalala also served as Trustee Professor of Political Science and Health Policy at the University of Miami, and was President of the Clinton Foundation from 2015 to 2017. <s> She was elected to the U.S. House of Representatives in the 2018 election, in a district which includes just over half of Miami as well as many of its eastern suburbs. <s> In March 2018, Shalala declared her candidacy in the Democratic primary for Florida's 27th congressional district. <s> The district voted overwhelmingly for Clinton in the 2016 presidential election, but its House seat was held by 30-year incumbent Republican Ileana Ros-Lehtinen.
simple: Donna Edna Shalala ( ; born February 14, 1941) is an American politician. <s> She is the United States representative of Florida's 27th congressional district since January 3, 2019. <s> She served as United States Secretary of Health and Human Services under President Bill Clinton from 1993 to 2001. <s> She was the president of the University of Miami, a private university in Coral Gables, Florida, from 2001 through 2015. <s> In August 2018, she became the Democratic nominee for Florida's 27th Congressional District.

title: Eileen Brennan
complex: Verla Eileen Regina Brennan (née Brennen; September 3, 1932 – July 28, 2013) was an American film, stage, and television actress. <s> She made her film debut in the satire "Divorce American Style" (1967), followed by a supporting role in Peter Bogdanovich's "The Last Picture Show" (1971), which earned her a BAFTA award nomination for Best Supporting Actress. <s> Brennan also worked prolifically in television, receiving Emmy nominations for her guest-starring roles on "Newhart", "Thirtysomething", "Taxi" and "Will & Grace". <s> Brennan was born Verla Eileen Regina Brennen on September 3, 1932, in Los Angeles, California, daughter of Regina "Jeanne" Menehan, a silent film actress, and John Gerald Brennen, a doctor. <s> Of Irish descent, she was raised Roman Catholic. <s> From 1968 to 1974, Brennan was married to British poet and photographer David John Lampson, with whom she had two sons: Patrick, a former basketball player turned actor, and Sam, a singer. <s> Brennan died at her home in Burbank, California, on July 28, 2013, of bladder cancer. <s> Her "Private Benjamin" costar Goldie Hawn said she was a "brilliant comedian, a powerful dramatic actress and had the voice of an angel."
simple: Eileen Brennan (September 3, 1932 – July 28, 2013) was a television, movie and theater actress. <s> She received Emmy nominations for guest starring roles on "Newhart" and "Will and Grace". <s> Brennan was born in Los Angeles, California on September 3, 1932. <s> She was married to David John Lampson from 1968 until they divorced in 1974. <s> Brennan died on July 28, 2013 in Burbank, California from bladder cancer, aged 80.

title: Service-oriented architecture
complex: Service-oriented architecture (SOA) is a style of software design where services are provided to the other components by application components, through a communication protocol over a network. <s> The basic principles of service-oriented architecture are independent of vendors, products and technologies.
simple: Service-oriented architecture (SOA) is a concept in computer programming.

title: Michael
complex: Michael is the name of an archangel in the Book of Daniel . <s> He is venerated in the Roman Catholic Church, the Oriental Orthodox Church, and the Eastern Orthodox Church.
simple: It is from the angel Michael in the Bible.

title: Ford Transit Connect
complex: The Ford Transit Connect is a compact panel van developed by Ford Europe. <s> It is built on a dedicated commercial vehicle platform and shares parts with the Ford Focus. <s> The first generation was designed by Peter Horbury and introduced in 2002 to replace the older Ford Escort and Fiesta-based van ranges, which had ceased production in the same year. <s> It has been imported to the North American market since the 2010 model year. <s> In North America, the Transit Connect does not have a direct predecessor; the closest vehicle to its size was the standard-length Ford Aerostar cargo van, which ceased production in 1997. <s> The Transit Connect Wagon was the first Ford minivan since the 2007 discontinuation of the Freestar, though it was closer in size to the standard length Ford Aerostar sold from 1986 to 1997.
simple: The Ford Transit Connect is a compact minivan developed by Ford Europe. <s> It has many of the same parts as the Ford Focus. <s> The first one was made to replace the Ford Escort and Ford Fiesta-based courier vans. <s> In Canada and the United States, the Transit Connect has no predecessor. <s> The closest vehicle to its size was the Ford Aerostar, which was last made in 1997. <s> In North America, the Transit Connect is Ford's first minivan since they stopped making the Ford Freestar in 2007.

title: Airdrieonians F.C.
complex: Airdrieonians Football Club are a Scottish professional football team based in Airdrie who are members of the Scottish Professional Football League (SPFL) and play in Scottish League One. <s> They were formed in 2002 as Airdrie United Football Club following the liquidation of the original club.
simple: Airdrie United Football Club is a Scottish professional football team. <s> They are based in the town of Airdrie, North Lanarkshire. <s> They are members of the Scottish Football League.

title: Financial Services (constituency)
complex: The Financial Services functional constituency is a functional constituency in the elections for the Legislative Council of Hong Kong first created in 1991. <s> The constituency is composed of 580 financial services participants. <s> These are, specifically, members of the Chinese Gold and Silver Exchange Society entitled to vote at general meetings, and participants of other exchange societies.
simple: The Financial Services, is a functional constituency in the elections for the Legislative Council of Hong Kong first created in 1998. <s> The constituency is composed of the members of the associations in the Financial Services Industry.

title: Armagnac
complex: Armagnac ( , ] ) is a distinctive kind of brandy produced in the Armagnac region in Gascony, southwest France. <s> It is distilled from wine usually made from a blend of grapes including Baco 22A, Colombard, Folle blanche and Ugni blanc, traditionally using column stills rather than the pot stills used in the production of cognac. <s> The resulting spirit is then aged in oak barrels before release. <s> Production is overseen by the Institut national de l'origine et de la qualité (INAO) and the Bureau National Interprofessionel de l'Armagnac (BNIA). <s> Armagnac is the oldest brandy distilled in France; and, in the past, it was consumed for its therapeutic benefits. <s> The Armagnac region lies between the Adour and Garonne rivers in the foothills of the Pyrenees. <s> The region was granted AOC status in 1936. <s> The official production area is divided into three districts that lie in the "departements" of Gers, Landes, and Lot-et-Garonne. <s> The region contains 15000 ha of grape-producing vines.
simple: Armagnac (; ]) is a kind of brandy produced in the Armagnac region of France. <s> It is then aged in oak barrels. <s> Armagnac is the oldest brandy distilled in France. <s> In the past was consumed for its therapeutic benefits. <s> The region lies between the Adour and Garonne rivers in the foothills of the Pyrenees. <s> It was given an AOC in 1936. <s> The area contains 15000 ha of grape-producing vines.

title: Málaga
complex: Málaga ( , ] ) is a municipality, capital of the Province of Málaga, in the Autonomous Community of Andalusia, Spain. <s> With a population of 571,026 in 2018, it is the second-most populous city of Andalusia and the sixth-largest in Spain. <s> The southernmost large city in Europe, it lies on the Costa del Sol ("Coast of the Sun") of the Mediterranean, about 100 km east of the Strait of Gibraltar and about 130 km north of Africa. <s> The painter and sculptor Pablo Picasso, Hebrew poet and Jewish philosopher Solomon Ibn Gabirol and the actor Antonio Banderas were born in Málaga. <s> The magnum opus of Cuban composer Ernesto Lecuona, "Malagueña", is named after the music of this region of Spain. <s> The climate is subtropical-Mediterranean (Köppen climate classification: "Csa") with very mild winters and hot summers. <s> Málaga enjoys plenty of sunshine throughout the year, with an average of about 300 days of sunshine and only about 40-45 with precipitation annually. <s> Its coastal location with winds blowing from the Mediterranean Sea make the heat manageable during the summer. <s> Málaga experiences the warmest winters of any European city with a population over 500,000. <s> The average temperature during the day in the period from December to February is 17 - . <s> During the winter, the Málaga Mountains ("Montes de Málaga") block out the cold weather from the north. <s> Generally, the summer season lasts about eight months, from April to November, although in the remaining four months temperatures sometimes surpass 24 °C . <s> Its average annual temperature is 23.3 °C during the day and 13.7 °C at night. <s> In the coldest month, January, the temperature ranges from 13 to during the day, 5 to at night and the average sea temperature is 16 - . <s> In the warmest month, August, the temperature ranges from 26 to during the day, above 20 °C at night and the average sea temperature is 26 °C . <s> Large fluctuations in temperature are rare. <s> The highest temperature ever recorded at the airport is 44.2 °C on 18 July 1978. <s> In the month of August 1881, the average reported daytime maximum temperature was a record 34.8 °C . <s> The coldest temperature ever recorded was -3.8 °C on the night of 4 February 1954. <s> The highest wind speed ever recorded was on 16 July 1980, measuring 119 km/h . <s> Snowfall is virtually unknown; since the end of the XIX century, Málaga city has only recorded snow one day in the 20th century, on 2 February 1954. <s> Annual average relative humidity is 65%, ranging from 58% in June to 72% in December. <s> Yearly sunshine hours is between 2,800 and 3,000 per year, from 5–6 hours of sunshine / day in December to average 11 hours of sunshine / day in July. <s> Rain occurs mainly in winter, with summer being generally dry. <s> Málaga is one of the few cities in Europe which are "green" all year round.
